    fun getArticleBody(article: ProductionArticle): String {
        return """
            PHARMACEUTICAL PRODUCTION & COMPLIANCE PORTAL
            REFERENCE CODE: ${article.code} | DEPARTMENT: PRODUCTION
            TECHNICAL DIVISION: ${article.category}
            STANDARD REFERENCE MANUAL (cGMP & 21 CFR Part 211 COMPLIANT)
            
            1.0 OBJECTIVE
            ${article.objective}
            
            2.0 SCOPE
            This production guidelines manual is applicable to all manufacturing steps, compounding runs, equipment operations, cleaning, line clearances, tooling, and packaging processes executed on the plant site under the Production Division. All technical staff, machine operators, supervisors, and line clearance auditors must strictly adhere to these criteria to ensure absolute compliance with current Good Manufacturing Practices (cGMP) and global regulatory expectations (FDA 21 CFR Part 211, WHO GMP guidelines).
            
            3.0 MATERIAL & EQUIPMENTS REQUIRED
            - cGMP-compliant machinery, production tooling (punch sets, die sets, dosing disks) with active status tags.
            - High-purity inputs (APIs, excipients, colorants, binder solutions, Water for Injection).
            - Calibrated in-process testing instruments (hardness testers, LOD moisture balances, disintegrators, check-weighers, metal detectors).
            - Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) including cleanroom gowns, steel-toed safety boots, face masks, ear defenders, safety goggles, and thermal gloves.
            - Approved cleaning solutions, lint-free wipes, swab rods, and purified rinse water.
            
            4.0 STEP-BY-STEP TECHNICAL PROCEDURE
            4.1 PRE-EXECUTION STEPS:
            - Before commencing any manufacturing operation, verify that the area and equipment hold active green 'CLEANED' labels and that the line clearance certificate has been officially signed by Quality Assurance.
            - Inspect the BMR (Batch Manufacturing Record) to verify lot numbers, target raw weights, and machine setpoints.
            - Complete safety checks, verify that static grounding clamps are connected, dust collection systems are active, and safety interlocks are fully functional.
            
            4.2 CORE PRODUCTION METHODOLOGY:
            - Carry out each step precisely in accordance with the Master Formula and Batch Manufacturing Record instructions. Do not deviate from validated parameters (rpm, temperature, spray rates, tampings).
            - Execute in-process controls (weight check, thickness, hardness, visual checks) at the defined frequencies (e.g., every 30 minutes). Record all physical parameters immediately and contemporaneously in the BMR.
            - If any critical alarm, metal detection, check-weigher reject, or tooling jam occurs, stop the machine immediately, isolate the affected material, and notify the production supervisor and QA.
            
            4.3 cGMP AND DATA INTEGRITY MANDATES:
            - All weights, machine printer slips, and analytical printouts must be affixed to the batch record and signed by both the operator and supervisor (double check verification).
            - Writing over entries, backdating, using pencil, or applying liquid correction fluid is strictly forbidden. Any error must be crossed out with a single clean line, corrected, initialed, dated, and accompanied by an explicit reason.
            
            5.0 SAFETY & ENVIRONMENTAL PRECAUTIONS
            - Always respect heavy machinery safety boundaries. Wear high-filtration dust masks or PAPR respirators when processing raw active powders to avoid inhalation.
            - Lock out tag out (LOTO) all machinery power sources before undertaking any mechanical cleaning, sifter screen shifts, or turret adjustments.
            - Collect all scrap blister foils, rejected tablets, and empty raw ingredient drums in locked bins for secure, weighed destruction.
            
            6.0 QUALITY AUDIT FREQUENCY
            This production standard guideline must be reviewed and re-verified on a biennial basis (every 2 years), or immediately upon any technical change control proposal, major machine upgrades, or regulatory audits.
            
            EFFECTIVE DATE: 2026-06-28
            AUTHOR: Lead Pharmaceutical Production Engineer
            REVIEWER: Solid Oral Dosage Block Manager
            APPROVER: Head of Production & Quality Operations
        """.trimIndent()
    }
